summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed, executed on the 15th day of June, A. D., 1898, by George J. Drummer and Esther J. Drummer, his wife, to the City of Seattle, for a perpetual right of way and easement over, through across and under a part of the N. W. 1/4 of the N. E. 1/4, and the N. E. 1/4 of the N. W. 1/4 of Section 22, Township 22 North, Range 6 East, W. M., in King County, Washington.
